CHAPTER XCVHI.

2. Pro se] “In their own favour.’

3. Ex copia rerum consilium trahit] “Drawn out his plans from the various resources before him ;” implying diffi- culty os choice rather than hesitation.

4. Neque minus] i. q. non minus.- ‘neque properly is equi- valent to et non ; but the copula is out of place here.
